div1.p:
Q. Did you afterwards change the twenty pound note? - A. Yes, at Mr. Drummond's, in Fleet-street, the following Monday, the 17th of August;
Charles Everitt
went with me.

Q. About what time in the day, as near as you can guess? - A. Between twelve and one, as near as I can guess; we bought two sixteenths and a quarter of the present English lottery that is to be drawn; I gave the twenty pound note to get change;
Charles Everitt
gave it to me; and I paid it.

WILLIAM BOUGH sworn. - I am one of the contractors for digging the docks at Blackwall;
John Holmes
is my partner; Hollis was my horsekeeper, and had free access to the provender to feed the horses; I believe nobody fed their horses as we did in that neighbourhood.(Confession of Thomas Hollis read:)
